
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        EXPOSE Instruction
                          Apache Server

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for Apache Web Server
    FROM httpd:latest
    COPY index.html /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/
    EXPOSE 80

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t apache .

3.  Run detached webserver container. 
    Map port 80 in container to port 1234 on host.

    $ docker run -d --name webserver -p 1234:80 apache

4.  Show ports for webserver container.

    $ docker port webserver
    80/tcp -> 0.0.0.0:1234

5.  Show HTML with curl localhost and port.

    $ curl localhost:1234
    <html>
    <body>
    <h1>Anderson Software Group, Inc.</h1>
        <h2><a href="https://asgteach.com/"
            title="Anderson Software Group, Inc.">
            https://asgteach.com</a>
        </h2>
    </body>
    </html>

6.  Show in browser with URL.

    http://localhost:1234

7.  Cleanup

    $ docker stop webserver
    $ docker container prune -f
